# LinkedIn Automation Integration for AgenticPilot

Add full LinkedIn OAuth connection, AI-powered post generation (via Gemini), and a polished dashboard page — mirroring the established Gmail automation patterns.

## Codebase Analysis Summary

After reading every file in `lib/gmail/`, `app/api/gmail/`, the Gmail dashboard page, the sidebar, middleware, `.env.local`, `lib/ai/llm.ts`, and `utils/supabase/server.ts`, here are the key patterns:

| Pattern | Gmail Implementation | LinkedIn Plan |
|---|---|---|
| Types | `lib/gmail/types.ts` — clean interfaces, no `any` | `lib/linkedin/types.ts` — same style |
| OAuth/Client | `lib/gmail/oauth.ts` + `lib/gmail/client.ts` | `lib/linkedin/client.ts` — single file (LinkedIn OAuth is simpler, no refresh) |
| API Routes | `app/api/gmail/{connect,callback,disconnect}/route.ts` | Same structure + `post/` and `posts/` routes |
| Dashboard | `app/dashboard/gmail/page.tsx` — `'use client'`, Suspense, sonner toasts, shadcn/ui | Mirror exactly |
| Supabase | `createClient(cookies())` from `@/utils/supabase/server` | Same |
| AI | `lib/ai/llm.ts` → `ChatGoogleGenerativeAI` (LangChain) | Use `getModel()` directly for post generation |
| Auth guard | Middleware protects `/dashboard/*` globally | Already covered — `/dashboard/linkedin` is protected |
| Sidebar | `components/shared/DashboardSidebar.tsx` — LinkedIn already listed! | **No sidebar change needed** — it's already there at line 52–57 |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The sidebar already has LinkedIn at `/dashboard/linkedin`. No modification required.

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> The existing `app/dashboard/linkedin/page.tsx` is a **hardcoded demo** with fake data. We will **replace it entirely** with a functional OAuth-connected page.

