#### [NEW] supabase/linkedin-schema.sql

SQL migration file containing:
- `linkedin_connections` table (uuid PK, user_id FK to auth.users, access_token, linkedin_person_urn, name, email, picture, expires_at, timestamps)
- `linkedin_posts` table (uuid PK, user_id FK, content, ai_generated, tone, scheduled_at, published_at, linkedin_post_id, status, error_message, timestamps)
- RLS enabled with `auth.uid() = user_id` policies
- `update_updated_at` trigger function (checks if it already exists first)

> [!NOTE]
> This is output as a `.sql` file for the user to run manually against Supabase, since we don't have Supabase CLI access.

---

#### [NEW] lib/linkedin/types.ts

Six interfaces/types:
- `LinkedInConnection` — maps 1:1 to `linkedin_connections` table columns
- `LinkedInPost` — maps 1:1 to `linkedin_posts` table columns
- `LinkedInTokenResponse` — `{ access_token: string; expires_in: number }`
- `LinkedInUserInfo` — `{ sub: string; name: string; email: string; picture: string }`
- `CreatePostPayload` — `{ topic?: string; tone?: string; aiGenerate: boolean; content?: string }`
- `PostStatus` — union type `'draft' | 'scheduled' | 'published' | 'failed'`

---

#### [NEW] lib/linkedin/client.ts

Constants and functions (all fully typed, zero `any`):

| Export | Description |
|---|---|
| `LINKEDIN_AUTH_URL` | `https://www.linkedin.com/oauth/v2/authorization` |
| `LINKEDIN_TOKEN_URL` | `https://www.linkedin.com/oauth/v2/accessToken` |
| `LINKEDIN_API_BASE` | `https://api.linkedin.com` |
| `LINKEDIN_SCOPES` | `['openid', 'profile', 'email', 'w_member_social']` |
| `getLinkedInAuthUrl(state)` | Builds full OAuth URL with response_type=code, correct scopes |
| `exchangeCodeForToken(code)` | POST to token URL, returns `LinkedInTokenResponse` |
| `getLinkedInUserInfo(accessToken)` | GET `/v2/userinfo`, returns `LinkedInUserInfo` |
| `createLinkedInPost(accessToken, personUrn, text)` | POST to `/v2/ugcPosts` with `X-Restli-Protocol-Version: 2.0.0` header |
| `isTokenExpired(expiresAt)` | Compares expiry timestamp to now |

> [!WARNING]
> Uses `/v2/ugcPosts` only — never `/v2/shares` (deprecated). Every LinkedIn API call includes `X-Restli-Protocol-Version: 2.0.0`.

